Regional risk and insurance managers are set to hold a one-day seminar in Nairobi tomorrow to deliberate on compliance in a fast-changing business regulatory environment.Hosted by publisher Commercial Risk Africa, the event will offer a platform for companies to exchange ideas on setting a disciplined risk management approach.The event, to be held at the Windsor Golf and Country Club, will bring together risk practitioners from across the region to meet with both local and international experts, to share best practices.The experts will address delegates on how to manage the rapid depreciation of African currencies, from a local and international perspective.They will explore political risk and violence, global legacy and sustainability, and broad financial risk issues.